System Documentation
====================

Utility functions
-----------------
	
	Class:	Card
			-Represents a UI card component fpr rendering content.
	Properties:
    		- title (private, string): The title of the card.
			- body (private, string): The body content of the card.
			- displayHeader (private, boolean): Indicates if the header should be displayed.
			- displayFooter (private, boolean): Indicates if the footer should be displayed.
			- footer (private, string): The footer content of the card.
	Parameters:
			displayHeader (Boolean):
				- Displays the card header section.
				- Default: True
			title (String):
				- The card text title.
			body (String):
				- The card body's content.
			displayFooter (Boolean):
				- Displays the card footer section.
				- Default: True
			footer (String):
				- The card footer's content.
	Methods:
				card.render()
					- returns a HTML template of the Card component.
				card.appendBodyContent()
					- add a HTML content to the cards body.

	
	Class:	Button
			- Creates a HTML button.
	Parameters:
			label (string):
				- button name or label.
			autofocus (boolean):
				- Specifies that a button should automatically get focus when the page loads.
				Default: false
			disable (boolean):
				- Specifies that a button should be disabled.
				Default: false
			name (string):
				- Specifies a name for the button
			type (string):
				- Specifies the type of button
				Options:
					- button
					- reset
					- submit
			value (string):
				- Specifies an initial value for the button
			class (string):
				- Specifies one or more classnames for an element.
			hidden (bool):
				- Specifies that an element is not yet, or is no longer, relevant.
				Default: false
			id (string):
				- Specifies a unique id for an element.
			onclick (string):
				- Script for mouse click on the element.
	Methods:
				button.render()
					- return a HTML button from button class instance.